		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'd like to know a few things about actual NESdev back when it was commercial that Neil Baldwin haven't mentionned in his blog yet (or if he did it was hiddedn in another subject). I'm pretty sure other people here burn to ask them too. Of course I can understand it's hard to impossible to remember exact details that much time later.
<br />
<br />- What kind of computer did you use to do NES-dev ? Did the compile process take long ?
<br />
<br />- What kind of tools did you have to make graphics ?
<br />
<br />- What kind of cardige hardware did you use to test your code in the console ? It looks all Eurocom's games uses the MMC3, were you only able to use a MMC3 cartridge ? Because you mentionned all the financial prolems Eurocom had, why didn't Eurocom try to save costs by having games running on simpler hardware like Rare did ?
<br />
<br />Feel free to answer either here or on your blog. Other people feel free to add questions to the list (but not too much or that may turn him down).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
