		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Celius wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Today, I find this to be a great alternative to learning a new programming language and using VB or something to build a nice level editor.</div>
<br />
<br />But with today's ease of tools like vb.net or even vb6 (or any flavor flavor of rad tool like delphi etc),  it will be a lot easier to make a simple editor and, the most important,  <strong>debug</strong> it later.  On the nes, making the same thing will be longer to code and will be always primitive since you're limited by the hardware and the controller for the input interface.
<br />
<br />Back in the days I could understand to do it on the nes and have a way to read your save ram but now I don't find it acceptable at all.

		

